#X text 64 46 the length of the random sequence can be increased beyond
16900 characters through a method i call 'no-input encryption' - treating
the ciphertext like plain text and creating a feedback loop between
the output and input. the exact length of a given sequence depends
on a number of variables \, such as the plain text seed \, initial
position of all four wheels \, and the wheel order. essentially \,
if when all wheels have rotated a full revolution and the next letter
is not the same as the initial letter \, the string continues for another
16900 characters until it matches. my own tests show that the maximum
string length is 25 * 16900 - a string of 26 * 16900 did not occur.
, f 73;
